certainly /ˈsɜːtənlɪ/

1. ADV You use certainly to emphasize what you are saying when you are making a statement. 的确; 无疑地 [ADV with cl/group] [强调] 

例： The public is certainly getting tired of hearing about it. 公众无疑厌倦了听这方面的事。 

例： The bombs are almost certainly part of a much bigger conspiracy. 几乎可以确定这些炸弹是一个更大阴谋的一部分。 

2. ADV You use certainly when you are agreeing with what someone has said. 当然 [ADV as reply] 

例： 'In any case you remained friends.'—'Certainly.' “不管怎样，你们还是朋友。”—“那当然。” 

3. ADV You say certainly not to say 'no' in a strong way. 当然不 [ADV as reply] [强调] 

例： 'Perhaps it would be better if I withdrew altogether.'—'Certainly not!' “我完全退出的话情况或许会好些。” — “当然不是。”

</div>

